<h1>Script: formulas-element</h1>
<p>
  The formulas-element must be contained in a definitions-element
 </p>

 <p> 
 This element loads formulas from an XML-file.
 The formulas may be in one of three forms:
 </p>
 <ul>
 <li>image (png,gif,jpg)</li>
 <li>mathml</li>
 <li>latex</li>
 </ul>
 <p>
  All this formulas is available by the PI <?_wxt xlink id="PIformula"?>
  and they will apear in formulalists, see PI <?_wxt xlink id="PIformulaList"?>.
 </p>
 <p>
  <em>image</em> and <em>latex</em> formulas will be presented as img. 
 </p>
 <p>
  The present version of WXT displays <em>mathml</em> formulas as MathML.
 </p>
 <p>
 See <?_wxt xlink id="aboutformulas"?> for a full description.
</p>

<pre class="prettyprint lang-html"><![CDATA[<formulas location=""/>]]>
</pre>

<table cellpadding="10px">

  <tr>
    <td  style="vertical-align:top"><strong>location</strong>(mandatory)</td>
    <td>The location of the document containg the formulas, absolute or relative to the script (anchor).
    </td>
  </tr>

</table>


<p>Examples:</p>
<pre class="prettyprint lang-html"><![CDATA[<formulas location="myformulas.xml"/>]]>
</pre>
<p>Example file:</p>
<div>
<?_wxt importtxt location="formula-sample.xml" lang="lang-xml"?>
</div>



